But ek important baat: statics methods me normally arrow function use nahi karte, kyunki arrow function ka apna this nahi hota.

Agar fetchAll ko arrow function se likhna hai, to aap aise kar sakte ho:

homeSchema.statics.fetchAll = () => {
  return mongoose.model('Home').find();
};


Bina $set ke — poora document replace ho sakta hai ⚠️
$set ke saath — sirf wahi fields update hongi jo tumne likhi hain ✅
await Home.findByIdAndUpdate(
  id,
  { $set: { houseName, price, location, image } }, // sirf ye fields touch karega
);





/*   ABOUT mongoose DELETE FUNCTION 

const house = await Home.deleteOne({ _id: homeId });
is misleading because house is not actually a house.

deleteOne() returns a result object, something like:

js

{
  acknowledged: true,
  deletedCount: 1
}

where deletedCount means how many documents were actually deleted from the database.
{(
    For deleteMany(), it can be bigger:
    
    const result = await Home.deleteMany({ location: "Delhi" });
    console.log(result.deletedCount);
    Maybe output:
    
    5
    Meaning 5 homes from Delhi were deleted.
)}


Better name:

js

const result = await Home.deleteOne({ _id: homeId });
Then you can check:

js

//used to check did home dlted successfully or not

if (result.deletedCount === 0) {
  console.log("No home found with this id");
} else {
  console.log("Home deleted successfully");
}

*/